CORRECTIONS:
1) @24:40 I said SARS-Cov-2 "shares most of its DNA....."   I should have said "gene sequence" not "DNA". SARS-Cov-2 is an RNA-based virus.

2) One poster who says he works in a lab that handles viruses says they're typically stored at around -80 decC, not -23 degC. I can't verify that, but either way I can confirm that they are deep frozen, and not likely to leak out of their sealed containers.
